contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox protected area of Australia | name = Frankland Group National Park | iucn_category = II | image = | caption = | locator_x = | locator_y = | nearest_town_or_city = | coordinates = {{Coord|17|09|49|S|146|00|42|E|type:landmark_region:AU-QLD|display=inline,title}} | area = {{Convert|0.77|km2|sqmi|2|abbr=on}} | established = 1994 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | managing_authorities = [[Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service]] | official_site = {{url|http://www.nprsr.qld.gov.au/parks/frankland-group/index.html}} }} '''Frankland Group''' is a national park in [[Queensland]], [[Australia]], 1353 km northwest of [[Brisbane]]. The five continental islands of the Franklin group are High, Normanby, Mabel, Round and Russel isles, which lie about 10 km offshore, and are about 45 km south east of [[Cairns, Queensland|Cairns]].<ref name=About>{{cite web|title=About The Franklands|url=http://www.nprsr.qld.gov.au/parks/frankland-group/about.html|publisher=The State of Queensland (Department of National Parks, Recreation, Sport and Racing)|accessdate=21 December 2012}}</ref> They are the traditional home of the Mandingalby Yindinji, and the Gungandji [[Australian Aboriginal|Aboriginal peoples]].<ref name=Index>{{cite web|title=Frankland Group National Park|url=http://www.nprsr.qld.gov.au/parks/frankland-group/index.html|publisher=The State of Queensland (Department of National Parks, Recreation, Sport and Racing)|accessdate=21 December 2012}}</ref> ==See also== {{Portal|Queensland}} * [[Protected areas of Queensland]] {{-}} ==References== {{reflist}} {{1stVoyageCookAus}} {{National Parks of Queensland}} [[Category:National parks of Far North Queensland]] [[Category:Protected areas established in 1994]] {{Queensland-national-park-stub}}
